        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:11PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 611 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cheraw Municipal Airport, or near Cheraw, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Hamlet, Ellerbe, Dobbins Heights, Lilesville, Morven,
McFarlan, Diggs, Blewett Falls Lake, and Derby.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
